mouth-to-mouth
resuscitation.

324
00:16:34,875 --> 00:16:36,500
It's what you have to do!

325
00:16:36,583 --> 00:16:38,625
Clear the victim's
air passage,

326
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:42,041
then hold his nose and place
your mouth over the top of his.

327
00:16:42,125 --> 00:16:45,000
I'm embarrassed,
but I can't stop!

328
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:46,458
Now, if you'll excuse me...

329
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:48,958
Mr. Sagara...

330
00:16:50,833 --> 00:16:51,791
Now just wait!

331
00:16:51,875 --> 00:16:53,250
Ah! What are you doing?

332
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:55,500
Oh, be quiet! Stop taking
advantage of the situation!

333
00:16:55,583 --> 00:16:57,708
It's mouth-to-mouth
resuscitation!

334
00:16:57,791 --> 00:16:58,916
Do you want him to die?

335
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,291
He doesn't need any;

336
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,291
he's been groaning ever
since we pulled him out!

337
00:17:02,375 --> 00:17:04,541
No! You're hearing things!

338
00:17:04,625 --> 00:17:06,666
Your psyche is so
vicious and twisted,

339
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:07,958
you'd rather see him die than--

340
00:17:08,041 --> 00:17:09,416
[SOUSUKE groans]

341
00:17:13,125 --> 00:17:14,541
[TESSA coughs]

342
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:18,291
Okay, now let's play it safe
around the water, everyone.

343
00:17:18,375 --> 00:17:19,500
[ALL groan]

344
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:21,875
Was it something I said?

345
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:23,958
Don't think you can
wrap this up like a PSA!

346
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:26,250
[KYOKO] Question:
Are Sousuke and Tessa

347
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:28,541
actually old acquaintances
or something?

348
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:29,583
Huh?

349
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:31,000
I mean, I may be wrong,

350
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:34,125
but it seems he's been
really concerned about Tessa.

351
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:35,541
Just look at him now.

352
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:37,625
[GIRL]
Yeah, it's strange...

353
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:40,041
Uh-huh. It's
anything but normal.

354
00:17:40,125 --> 00:17:42,375
Yes, you're right.
Let me tell you the story

355
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:43,833
behind all this.

356
00:17:43,916 --> 00:17:47,333
The truth is, my father,
Ricardo Testarossa

357
00:17:47,416 --> 00:17:52,166
and Mr. Sagara's foster father,
Andre Preminin are old friends.

358
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:54,541
Because of that,
from a young age,

359
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:57,041
I often played with Mr. Sagara.

360
00:17:57,125 --> 00:17:59,291
[ALL] Ooh...

361
00:17:59,375 --> 00:18:02,875
That's why... in my eyes...

362
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:06,250
He is... well...

363
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:09,791
Really just a... a special boy!

364
00:18:09,875 --> 00:18:11,708
[GIRLS giggle &amp; squeal]

365
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:14,500
Uh-oh. Looks like
Kaname's got a rival.

366
00:18:14,583 --> 00:18:16,125
What was that?!

367
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:18,666
You're okay!

368
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:20,833
[KYOKO]
Hey! Hey, Sousuke!

369
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:22,375
Yes, what?

370
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:26,208
Tell me, do you and Tessa really
have a special relationship?

371
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,625
Yeah. I can't be
more specific, but...

372
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:36,583
it's something that you couldn't
even begin to imagine.

373
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:39,250
Oh, such boldness!

374
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:42,333
Please, don't
tease me like that.

375
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:44,041
Tease you?

376
00:18:44,125 --> 00:18:45,291
What's going on?

377
00:18:45,375 --> 00:18:46,250
Don't ask me!

378
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:47,958
[SOUSUKE]
Huh? Kaname!

379
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:55,583
[phone rings]

380
00:18:55,666 --> 00:18:58,041
Oh, you really mean
you'll take me there?

381
00:18:58,125 --> 00:18:59,708
--[KALININ] It's me.
--[GIRL] Yeah, come with us!

382
00:18:59,791 --> 00:19:01,333
[SOUSUKE] Lieutenant Commander
Kalinin, what's going on?

383
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:03,625
--I'm already at my wit's end!
--She's right, the food's great.

384
00:19:03,708 --> 00:19:04,958
[KALININ]
There's nothing to explain.

385
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:07,125
Now, I do sympathize
with you, but--

386
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:10,083
Too slow! You can cut
that time by five seconds!

387
00:19:10,166 --> 00:19:11,625
Try again!

388
00:19:11,708 --> 00:19:14,958
So, anyway, please see
that she's well attended to.

389
00:19:15,041 --> 00:19:16,750
[SOUSUKE]
But sir, I can't do it alone!

390
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:20,000
[KALININ] Don't worry, Sergeant
Major Mao is on her way.

391
00:19:20,083 --> 00:19:21,958
She should be arriving
at the stop-over

392
00:19:22,041 --> 00:19:23,708
in Hachijojima any minute now.

393
00:19:23,791 --> 00:19:25,708
She'll arrive at your
location this evening.

394
00:19:25,791 --> 00:19:27,083
That's definite?

395
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,583
[KALININ]
Take it easy tonight.

396
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:30,583
That is all.

397
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:32,208
[SOUSUKE sighs]

398
00:19:33,916 --> 00:19:35,291
[SOUSUKE]
Huh?

399
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:43,625
[cell phone rings]

400
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:44,291
Yes?

401
00:19:44,375 --> 00:19:46,083
Yeah, hello!

402
00:19:46,166 --> 00:19:47,833
Hey, it's me, Mao!

403
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:49,458
[SOUSUKE]
Mao? What's your position?

404
00:19:49,541 --> 00:19:52,041
[MAO]
I'm in Hachijojima right now!

405
00:19:52,125 --> 00:19:54,791
It looks like there's a
typhoon approaching!

406
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:57,666
I'm afraid all the flights
to Tokyo have been cancelled.

407
00:19:57,750 --> 00:19:58,916
[SOUSUKE]
What? Can you repeat?

408
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:01,583
[MAO] Cancelled!
They've been cancelled!

409
00:20:01,666 --> 00:20:03,708
So I'm gonna be
spending the night here.

410
00:20:03,791 --> 00:20:06,166
You take care of Tessa
for me, okay?

411
00:20:06,250 --> 00:20:07,500
[SOUSUKE]
Hold on, you can't...

412
00:20:07,583 --> 00:20:10,166
[MAO] Oh that's right,
it's just the two of you.

413
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,875
You can jump her
bones if you like.

414
00:20:11,958 --> 00:20:13,083
You have my permission.

415
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:14,666
Ooh, ya lady-killer, you.

416
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:17,250
[SOUSUKE] Mao, you're turning
your back on a fellow soldier?

417
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,458
[MAO]
See ya! Good luck!

418
00:20:19,541 --> 00:20:21,375
[SOUSUKE]
Wait, come in Urzu 2! Respond!

419
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:23,875
Requesting immediate
backup! Urzu 2!

420
00:20:33,458 --> 00:20:34,291
[SOUSUKE]
Kaname?

421
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:35,458
Yeah, what?

422
00:20:35,541 --> 00:20:37,541
This may sound strange, but...

423
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,291
Well if you wouldn't
mind it, I would like

424
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:41,833
